cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS 

The paper deals with the optimization of neural networks for binary classification tasks, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures (cs.DS). The paper focuses on the theoretical justification of limiting the network size within finite bounds for optimization, which is a common problem in machine learning and neural networks. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.DS.
